Specification 
Overview 
 
For this individual assignment, you will implement WebAI using a pre-trained 
TensorFlow.js model.  
 
Description 
 
This open-ended assignment encourages creativity. It challenges you to build a 
browser-based web application that performs real-time object detection using 
TensorFlow.js.  You will use TensorFlow.js pre-trained COCO-SSD model for 
object detection (model paths: https://github.com/tensorflow/tfjs-
models/tree/master/coco-ssd).  Use your imagination to create an interesting 
application, whether it's for smart home monitoring, traffic monitoring, or any other 
concept you can envision. 
 
 
Tasks: 
 
Develop a single webpage (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) to allow real-time object 
detection in a specific context of application. This web page must be named as 
index.html 
 
Minimum requirements 
 
• Write client-side JavaScript to implement the application logic. This code 
must process media inputs using the TensorFlow.js COCO-SSD model to 
enable a specific, chosen application.  
• Can load the COCO-SSD model and detect objects on at least one input 
mode (e.g., image upload or webcam or both). 
• For each detected object, draw a bounding box and display its class 
label and confidence scores. 
• Display the results in ‘user-friendly’ format on the index.html page 
• Code a Node Express server to serve this index.html as a static page (i.e. 
place in a folder called “public”). 
• Provides basic instructions for handling errors (e.g., denied camera 
permissions). 
 
Note: Submissions that do not meet all minimum requirements may receive a 
maximum of 50/100. 
 
P1. Essential Features (40 marks): 
 
• Model Integration (10 marks) 
o Load model at startup with a visible loading state  
o Warmup pass to pre-allocate tensors 
o Clean-up / dispose tensors and avoid leaks  
o Version/model meta-data panel (name, size)  
• Media Inputs (10 marks) 
o Webcam stream with start/stop controls  
o Static image/video upload/drag-drop and rerun detection  
o Note: You are free to implement both above, but you don’t have to! 
• Rendering & UI (10 marks) 
o Canvas overlay with boxes, labels, confidences  
o Class filter toggle (show/hide selected classes)  
o Confidence threshold slider  
• Performance & Responsiveness (10 marks) 
o FPS (frame-per-second) counter and simple timing display  
o Device/backend selector (CPU/WebGL; WebGPU optional)  
o Responsive layout (mobile/tablet/desktop)  
 
